                       St. Louis Post-Dispatch (Missouri)

                 July 23, 1999, Friday, FIVE STAR LIFT EDITION

BARNES-JEWISH RANKS SEVENTH ON LIST OF TOP U.S. HOSPITALS

SECTION: METRO, Pg. B1

LENGTH: 105 words


Barnes-Jewish Hospital ranked seventh overall on U.S. News & World Report's
annual list of the best hospitals in the country, earning the highest ranking of
the four St. Louis area hospitals on the rating.

Judged by ability in 16 categories including cancer, psychiatry and geriatrics,
Barnes-Jewish placed on the ranking's honor roll for the seventh straight time.
It scored high in 14 treatment categories. The other institutions included St.
Louis University Hospital, which ranked high in nine treatment categories; St.
John's Mercy Medical Center (three categories); and St. Anthony's Medical Center
(one category).

LOAD-DATE: July 23, 1999

LANGUAGE: English

